# NOTES-TO-ADMIN — {{PROJECT_NAME}}

Surfaced by prompt-to-production for items requiring admin input or awareness. See `references/notes-to-admin-guide.md`.

## Severity meanings

- **BLOCKER** — Cannot proceed without admin input. Always paired with a paused task / phase flag in PLAN.md.
- **IMPORTANT** — Can proceed (with non-dependent work), but admin should weigh in soon.
- **FYI** — Informational only.

## Entry format

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD — [SEVERITY]

**Issue:** [what is happening, 1–2 sentences]

**What I need from you:** [concrete ask; name the options]

**Affected work:** [PLAN.md phase / task affected — required for BLOCKER]

**Non-dependent work in progress:** [what continues while this is open]

**Resolution:** _(appended by admin)_
```

## Resolution mechanic

Append `**Resolution:** YYYY-MM-DD — [decision / action taken]` to an entry to resolve it. Entries are never deleted, only resolved — the history is the audit trail.

